transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yeah, how are you doing, this is Greg, who am I speaking with?

Speaker 1: My name is Joe, I can help you.

Speaker 2: Joe, I ordered this Viagra, you know, the new one out, the last of 14 hours, you take—

Speaker 1: It in 14 minutes, it gives you an erection or whatever it is, right?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Hello?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Hello?

Speaker 2: I'm still here, sir, how can we help you?

Speaker 1: Well, it's the wrong, you sent me the wrong one, you sent me, send us the, the, the—

Speaker 2: Yeah, what's the zip code to pull up your profile, sir?

Speaker 1: Sure.

Speaker 2: Here, what's the zip code?

Speaker 1: 11701.

Speaker 2: 11701?

Speaker 1: 11701, yes.

Speaker 2: And your first and last name?

Speaker 1: Greg Frederick.

Speaker 2: Is it Gregory or is it Greg legally?

Speaker 1: It's Gregory, it's the legal name.

Speaker 2: Got it, so I pulled you up here.

Speaker 1: So the latest order you received should have been the AGB Viagra, what does the marking—

Speaker 2: On the pill say?

Speaker 1: You want the drug number or on the pill itself?

Speaker 2: The marking on the pill, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, it says on the pill is 100, so that's the milligrams, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's going to be the AGB, sir.

Speaker 2: The one that's not the AGB says AC on there.

Speaker 1: The one you receive is going to be the AGB because it only shows the dosages.

Speaker 2: All right, so I disregard saying this is generic for Viagra.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's authorized generic Viagra is the full name for the AGB.

Speaker 2: It's a step up higher than a standard generic Viagra.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Okay, I just wanted to make sure because I've used this before, the other one I tried.

Speaker 2: You might have used the generic, but not an authorized one.

Speaker 1: This is a step up higher.

Speaker 2: You'll see how the benefits of these are more efficient.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I take your word for it.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: You have a good day now, sir.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Bye.
